title: Getting Started
author: space_fountain
pages:
#- So you've decided you want to move to Aurora. What now? The first step will be moving in. We have a fully funtional hotel at 4416, -1560. Ask around. Once you've been in town for a bit you'll probably want to apply for citizenship. Post a request in the 
#- sub (/r/CivAgora) and if no on objects you'll be a citizen in 72 hours. In the rare case that there is contestation a vote will be called which will take 48 hours. If by the end of that time you have secured 2/3 of the vote you're officially a Citizen
As
#- a citizen you'll be allowed to vote on city issues and for the Chancellor every month. You'll also be allowed one free plot in the City of Aurora. Ask the Chancellor and they or one they designate will provide you with one.

Your house
#- may have to follow some building rules though no such rules may apply retrospectively.

Once you settle into Aurora you'll probably need to find your way arround. See https://i.imgur.com/IiG3ne1.jpg. All locations noted on the map are 
#- free for public use, though for many such as the factory a donation is strongly suggested to aid in their upkeep. Similarly all farms must be replanted.

There are always projects being worked on. check the sub frequently and don't
#- be afraid to ask questions in game or on Mumble. We don't bite.

Have a good time and welcome to Aurora
#- 